parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the VP44 fuel injection pump can cause loss of power, white smoke, and stalling, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
The improperly welded driveline on the transmission can cause the tube and flange to turn within itself, leading to transmission failure, loss of power, and potential accidents.
symptoms: The driveline on the transmission fails
the tube and flange turn within itself
the transmission does not function properly
unusual noises or vibrations from the transmission.
